"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-noah-lyles-olympics-100m-final-result-2024-b2591133.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  The American stole victory on the finish line in Paris to add Olympic gold to his world title and cement his status as the fastest man on the planet  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 220, \"end\": 228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.998585496609584, \"rank\": 0.001092557194406331, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 265, \"end\": 270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.20207603366951e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  World champion, Olympic champion.Noah Lylestalked an awful lot of talk in the build-up toParis 2024, but he backed up the bluster with a late, late burst on the Stade de France track, surging past the field to pip them all on the line.\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 731, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There can be no argument now.\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What's the title of the Olympic champion?\\\"\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 805, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles said, referring to the 'fastest man on the planet' tag that goes with gold.\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 887, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 806, \"end\": 811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999506493431612, \"rank\": 4.879930778482946e-05, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Amen.\\\"\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It does not matter that he did not get near the world record he said he'd break,finishing in 9.79 sec; or that it came down to five thousandths of a second, less time than it takes the human eye to blink; or that he finished second in his heat and his semi-final too.\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 1164, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles delivered when it mattered most.\", \"from\": 1165, \"to\": 1203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jamaica's Kishane Thompson had been burdened with the title of heir to Usain Bolt after running the fastest time this year, and he led for 99m of this race.\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1205, \"end\": 1212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999997239684, \"rank\": 2.7624701062743296e-10, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 1223, \"end\": 1231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9869196950386334, \"rank\": 0.013253665141780406, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 1276, \"end\": 1286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Usain Bolt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Lyles fought back from dead last at 40m, and they crossed the line together.\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1442, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thompson roared in celebration but his face dropped when the giant screen displayed \\\"photo finish\\\" by his name.\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1444, \"end\": 1452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9869196950386334, \"rank\": 0.013253665141780406, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They stared up from purgatory, waiting for the verdict.\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1611, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Kishane, I think you got it, man,\\\" Lyles told Thompson, with a pat on the shoulder.\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1660, \"end\": 1668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9869196950386334, \"rank\": 0.013253665141780406, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thompson looked pained.\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1699, \"end\": 1707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9869196950386334, \"rank\": 0.013253665141780406, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Come on, man!\\\"\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1738, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"he shouted at the screen, urging it to move.\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1783, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Come on, man!\\\"\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1799, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles paced with his hands on his head.\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1840, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then the result came and Lyles was off again, one moment ripping the name from his chest and raising it to the gods, the next streaking across the hammer field with the stars and stripes flapping in the wind.\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 2049, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1866, \"end\": 1871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999506493431612, \"rank\": 4.879930778482946e-05, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thompson was awarded silver as Lyles' US teammate Fred Kerley took bronze.\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2050, \"end\": 2058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9869196950386334, \"rank\": 0.013253665141780406, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 2081, \"end\": 2086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999506493431612, \"rank\": 4.879930778482946e-05, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 2088, \"end\": 2090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9968021375086434, \"rank\": 0.0015872638649378763, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2100, \"end\": 2111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Kerley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was prepared to see his name pop up,\\\" Lyles said.\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2178, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I saw my name pop up and I said, 'Goodness gracious, I am incredible'.\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2250, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the one I wanted.\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the hard battle, the amazing opponents, everybody was healthy and came to fight.\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am the wolf among wolves.\\\"\", \"from\": 2360, \"to\": 2388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles is the closest thing athletics has right now to a global superstar.\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2463, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was placed front and centre of the Netflix documentarySprint, which aimed to sprinkle a little of theDrive to Survivemagic in athletics' direction.\", \"from\": 2464, \"to\": 2614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2502, \"end\": 2509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netflix\", \"score\": 0.9999999999949978, \"rank\": 5.041851772781525e-12, \"text\": \"Netflix\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netflix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netflix\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a sport always fighting for attention, for a more permanent place in the entertainment-scape.\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2714, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He embraced the role with extreme main-character energy.\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2772, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am the third fastest human to ever live,\\\" he bragged in one of the opening scenes.\", \"from\": 2773, \"to\": 2858, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Soon to be the first.\\\"\", \"from\": 2859, \"to\": 2882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His swagger was not always endearing but it was undeniably compelling.\", \"from\": 2884, \"to\": 2954, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He spoke with raw honesty about the torment of failing in the spotlight, and about the depression he suffered.\", \"from\": 2955, \"to\": 3065, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So when he looked into the camera and said he would become Olympic champion, you knew he meant it.\", \"from\": 3066, \"to\": 3164, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Another quote ran: \\\"I am a true believer that the moment is not bigger than me, the moment was made for me.\\\"\", \"from\": 3166, \"to\": 3274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, this was his moment.\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3302, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The US prides itself on its dominance in track and field but an American had not won this race for 20 years, not since Justin Gatlin in Athens.\", \"from\": 3303, \"to\": 3446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3307, \"end\": 3309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9968021375086434, \"rank\": 0.0015872638649378763, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3367, \"end\": 3375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.998585496609584, \"rank\": 0.001092557194406331, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3439, \"end\": 3445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.938416622982769, \"rank\": 0.06562477209785587, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bolt won the next three in Beijing, London and Rio before Italy's Lamont Marcell Jacobs stunned the world in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 3447, \"to\": 3562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3474, \"end\": 3481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999993890080124, \"rank\": 6.109924666150839e-07, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3483, \"end\": 3489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999982310328, \"rank\": 1.769063420294406e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 3494, \"end\": 3497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999567542937967, \"rank\": 4.324757656751759e-05, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3505, \"end\": 3510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9625548609275496, \"rank\": 0.030347011042017525, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3520, \"end\": 3534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marcell Jacobs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\"}, {\"begin\": 3556, \"end\": 3561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.5814190722396052, \"rank\": 0.7199298163929614, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jacobs finished fifth here in 9.85 sec, behind South Africa's Akani Simbine who came fourth in 9.82.\", \"from\": 3563, \"to\": 3663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3610, \"end\": 3622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999982112415264, \"rank\": 9.219363139953196e-07, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 3625, \"end\": 3638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One by one, Lyles picked them all off.\", \"from\": 3665, \"to\": 3703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3677, \"end\": 3682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999506493431612, \"rank\": 4.879930778482946e-05, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was hard for me to picture where we were, and I guess that was a good thing,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3705, \"to\": 3795, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was fortunate to have [Jamaica's] Oblique Seville next to me because all throughout the year he's been hitting that acceleration that I wasn't hitting.\", \"from\": 3796, \"to\": 3950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3822, \"end\": 3829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999997239684, \"rank\": 2.7624701062743296e-10, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I wasn't going to let him go.\\\"\", \"from\": 3951, \"to\": 3981, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thompson hoped to be the first Jamaican man since Bolt to win a global 100m title.\", \"from\": 3983, \"to\": 4065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3983, \"end\": 3991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9869196950386334, \"rank\": 0.013253665141780406, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 4014, \"end\": 4022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9641778188443247, \"rank\": 0.037153085691725395, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am a bit disappointed but I am super happy and grateful at the same time,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4153, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wasn't patient enough with my speed and myself, I should have let my speed bring me to the line.\", \"from\": 4154, \"to\": 4253, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have learned from it.\", \"from\": 4254, \"to\": 4277, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I could not see Noah, but I think he could see me and said, 'hey, Kishane, I thought you got it'.\", \"from\": 4278, \"to\": 4375, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4294, \"end\": 4298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\", \"score\": 0.9999639341423152, \"rank\": 2.5120388882057354e-05, \"text\": \"Noah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he was too far to my right so I wasn't sure.\", \"from\": 4376, \"to\": 4424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is my closest race.\", \"from\": 4425, \"to\": 4449, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was that close.\\\"\", \"from\": 4450, \"to\": 4469, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For Lyles, this could be just the start.\", \"from\": 4471, \"to\": 4511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4475, \"end\": 4480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999506493431612, \"rank\": 4.879930778482946e-05, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He still has the 200m to come, his strongest event, as well as a 4x100m showdown with the Jamaicans.\", \"from\": 4512, \"to\": 4612, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is plenty more,\\\" he promised.\", \"from\": 4614, \"to\": 4650, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope you guys like Noah because I have got a lot more coming.\\\"\", \"from\": 4651, \"to\": 4716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4673, \"end\": 4677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\", \"score\": 0.9999639341423152, \"rank\": 2.5120388882057354e-05, \"text\": \"Noah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 4718, \"to\": 4948, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4769, \"end\": 4780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.04420726441831e-23, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"